OL,3,CInspections of coastal defences met
OL,4,Cwith concern by seafront businesses
OL,6,FSimon Allum, owner of Pinquay's Bar on
OL,7,FSt Peter Port's seafront, argues that
OL,8,Fnot enough is being done to adequately
OL,9,Fprotect local businesses against
OL,10,Ffloods and high tides in town.
OL,12,FBusinesses in Guernsey's harbour area
OL,13,Fare often vulnerable to flooding
OL,14,Fduring periods of bad weather or
OL,15,Fexceptionally high tides.
OL,17,FSimon has had to invest in
OL,18,F'floodgates' to protect his bar: but
OL,19,Fthese don't always work.
